FBIS3-51932 "drlat018_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-018 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Jan 1994 Haiti Netherlands Antilles Clinton State-of-Union Address Reported FL2601212794 Bonaire Trans World Radio in English 1100 GMT 26 Jan 94 FL2601212794 Bonaire Trans World Radio Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In his first State of the Union address, United States President Bill Clinton, has repeated his call for reform of both his nation's health care and welfare. He said he would veto any bill that does not contain universal health coverage. He also called for action to reduce crime and urged a ban on assault rifles. Public opinion polls s how that a majority of Americans liked the president's speech. The oposition leader in the Senate, Bob Dole, used charts to suggest that Mr. Clinton's healthcare reform plan means more governmental control.
